This paper is focused on deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that has seen significant growth in recent years. The paper investigates the complexities of off-policy deep RL algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experimental setup involves Atari 2600 games, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be relevant. Additionally, the paper explores the trade-off between exploration and exploitation, which is a common theme in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
